\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22 \pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs40\b\cf2 Lucie: Salesforce Doc Generator\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs40\b\cf2 Usage guide for Squads, Tech Leads and the Design Review\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs22 This document explains step-by-step how Squads, Tech Leads and the Design Review use Lucie to produce, share and leverage a high-quality Salesforce documentation. It emphasises the benefits brought by the tool and the collaborative aspect across the team.\par
\page
\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs40\b\cf2 1. Overview\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs22 Lucie is an internal tool that analyses a Salesforce org and produces: a complete HTML documentation (objects, Apex, Flows, OmniStudio, permissions), detailed Excel workbooks (data dictionary, profiles, permission sets, inventory, PMD violations) and two Word documents (a data dictionary and a summary holding prioritised advice).\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs22 Three audiences use Lucie:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Squads: to quickly explore the metadata, prepare a story or validate the impact of a delivery.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Tech Leads: to drive technical quality, follow the org evolution sprint after sprint and feed cross-cutting reviews.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Design Review: to rely on a standardised support to arbitrate and prioritise the actions to take.\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs22 The generated documentation is centralised in a shared folder so everyone works on the same body of knowledge.\par
\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs40\b\cf2 2. Key benefits\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Automated, standardised documentation: no more manual maintenance of the data dictionary, the Apex/Flow pages or the permission set list.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Prioritised advice: the Word summary lists actions sorted by severity then by occurrence count. The most impactful items appear first.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Adopt vs Adapt score: a synthetic indicator to compare the level of customisation across orgs or over time.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Anti-pattern detection: static analysis rules inspired by PMD, the Salesforce Well-Architected Framework and the Architect Decision Guides.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Multilingual: generation in French or English depending on the UI language.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Built-in AI assistant: discuss the analysed org with Claude or Gemini.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Native collaboration: shareable configuration (weights, rules, exclusions), shared output folder, format suited to meeting minutes.\par
\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs40\b\cf2 3. Setup and shared configuration\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs22 Before rolling Lucie out to the Squads, the technical owner sets up a shared reference configuration.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 3.1 Installation\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 1.\tab Clone the repository.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 2.\tab Install dependencies: pip install -r requirements.txt.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 3.\tab (Optional) Install Salesforce CLI (sf) and PMD for the built-in features.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 4.\tab Run the application: python app.py.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 3.2 Shared configuration\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs22 In the configuration screen, the team agrees on:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab The shared output folder (network share, OneDrive or SharePoint accessible to every Squad).\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab The exclusion file (exclusion.xlsx), versioned and used by every Squad to homogenise results.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab The PMD ruleset (optional), versioned in the same shared repository.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab The static analysis rules (rules.xml): validate the enabled rules through the "Analysis rules" tab.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Scoring weights and Adopt vs Adapt weights: standardised, otherwise scores stop being comparable across Squads.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab The interface language (FR or EN), which drives the language of the generated Word documents.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab The "Generate the Data Dictionary Word document" and "Generate the summary Word document" toggles: ticked by default, leave them on so Design Review has its inputs.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab AI API keys (Claude, Gemini): personal, kept in each user's individual configuration.\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\li567\ri567\i\cf3\fs22 Tip: versioning exclusion.xlsx, rules.xml and the PMD ruleset in a shared Git repository ensures consistent analyses across all Squads.\i0\cf1\par
\page
\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs40\b\cf2 4. How Squads use the tool\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs22 Each Squad uses Lucie for everyday needs: exploring the org, preparing a story, auditing before a release.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 4.1 Standard run\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 1.\tab Open Lucie via python app.py.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 2.\tab Pick the source folder (Salesforce retrieve output or clone of the Squad repo).\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 3.\tab Pick the shared output folder, in a Squad-specific dated subfolder (e.g. \\\\share\\lucie\\squad-alpha\\2026-04-25).\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 4.\tab Load the Salesforce org: either via Web login + alias then Generate manifest and Run retrieve, or directly via the Manifest + Retrieve + Doc button which chains everything.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 5.\tab Click Generate documentation.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 6.\tab Open the HTML index and explore the generated docs.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 4.2 Recommended use cases\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Onboarding a new joiner: the HTML documentation provides an instant map of the org (objects, flows, Apex classes, permissions).\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Preparing a story: open the data dictionary Word document or the page of the impacted object to identify existing fields, record types and rules.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Pre-release audit: generate the docs before delivery and compare the Word summary with the previous run to spot new findings.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Quick check: ask the AI assistant (Discussion tab) about the org instead of digging through code.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 4.3 Squad guidelines\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Run the generation before each sprint review to have a stable baseline.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Store the documentation in the shared folder: other Squads and Design Review will rely on it.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab React quickly to the Critical and Major findings of the Word summary; they are the first to surface in Design Review.\par
