\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs40\b\cf2 5. How Tech Leads use the tool\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs22 The Tech Lead drives the technical quality of their Squad and feeds the cross-cutting reviews led by the manager.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 5.1 Tooling responsibilities\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Maintain the shared configuration (analysis rules, exclusion file, scoring weights).\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Make sure the Squad generates the documentation at least once per sprint.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Review the findings raised and organise their treatment with the Squad.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Surface to the manager the topics that go beyond the Squad boundaries and deserve a Design Review.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 5.2 Typical sprint workflow\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 1.\tab Beginning of sprint: pull the latest generation stored in the shared folder as a reference baseline.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 2.\tab During the sprint: launch an intermediate analysis on a major refactor (new object, Apex refactor, Flow migration).\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 3.\tab End of sprint: generate the full documentation and archive it in the shared folder (dated subfolder).\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 4.\tab Prepare the retrospective / sprint review: pull the 3 to 5 highest-priority actions from the Word summary.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 5.\tab Prepare the Design Review: surface to the manager the cross-cutting findings and arbitration topics.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 5.3 Indicators to watch\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Customisation score evolution sprint after sprint.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Adopt vs Adapt score evolution.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Findings volume per severity (Critical, Major, Minor, Info).\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Top 5 triggered rules, visible in the Advice chapter of the Word summary.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Number of objects and fields actually documented (data dictionary).\par
\page
\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs40\b\cf2 6. Use in Design Review\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\fs22 The Design Review combines outputs produced by every Squad to take coordinated architecture decisions. This is where the Word summary and its Advice chapter shine.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 6.1 Before the meeting\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 1.\tab The manager (Design Review host) gathers from the shared folder the summary.docx of every Squad, the matching data_dictionary.docx and the HTML index for technical details.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 2.\tab Preliminary read of the Advice chapter of every summary.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 3.\tab Selection of actions to debate, prioritising Critical and Major ones.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 4.\tab Building the agenda from that selection.\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 6.2 During the meeting\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 1.\tab Walk through the Word summary: cover page, overview, customisation metrics, then Advice chapter.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 2.\tab For each priority action, discuss the finding with the concerned Squad.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 3.\tab Decide the action: fix now, documented exception or deferred with deadline.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 4.\tab Assign the responsible Squad and action owner.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 5.\tab If needed, open the data dictionary Word document or HTML documentation to double-check a technical detail.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 6.\tab Capture each decision in the meeting minutes by quoting the rule identifier (for example APEX-SEC-001).\par
\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs30\b\cf2 6.3 After the meeting\b0\cf1\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Store the meeting minutes next to the analysed documentation in the shared folder.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab Minutes refer to findings from the Word summary, which makes decisions replayable.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa80\sl276\slmult1\fs22 \bullet\tab At the next Design Review, verify the decrease in occurrence count for every treated finding and acknowledge the Squads that progressed.\par
